Don Lope de Aguirre, a brutal,ruthless and insane conquistador leads his soldiers into the Amazon jungle in an obsessive quest for gold. The story is of the expedition's relentless degeneration into brutality and despair

A few decades after the destruction of the Inca empire, a Spanish expedition leaves the mountains of Peru and goes down the Amazon river in search of gold and wealth. Soon, they come across great difficulties and Don Aguirres, a ruthless and insane man who cares only about riches, becomes their leader. As the spanish conquistadors battle starvation,Disease native Indians, the forces of nature, and each other, Don Lope de Aguirre (Klaus Kinski), &quot;The Wrath of God,&quot; is consumed with visions of conquering all of South America and leads his army down a treacherous river on a doomed quest into oblivion.

